    <div id="overview" class="section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>The Workshop System is a comprehensive component of the Comserv application designed to manage educational workshops, presentations, and related materials. It currently supports advertising workshops, but will evolve into a complete platform where users can create and manage their own workshops.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div id="vision" class="section">
        <h2>Future Vision</h2>
        <p>The Workshop System will evolve from its current state as an advertising platform into a full-featured workshop management system where:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Registered users can create their own workshops</li>
            <li>Workshop creators can upload and manage presentation materials</li>
            <li>Users can register for workshops and receive notifications</li>
            <li>Presenters can track attendance and participation</li>
            <li>Interactive workshops can be conducted directly through the platform</li>
            <li>Workshop materials can be organized in a searchable database</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div id="documentation" class="section">
        <h2>Documentation Structure</h2>
        <p>Workshop System documentation is organized into the following sections:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/documentation/workshops/user_guide">User Guide</a> - How to use the Workshop System</li>
            <li><a href="/documentation/workshops/admin_guide">Administrator Guide</a> - Managing workshops and presentations</li>
            <li><a href="/documentation/workshops/technical">Technical Documentation</a> - Implementation details</li>
            <li><a href="/documentation/workshops/presentations">Presentation System</a> - Working with presentation materials</li>
            <li><a href="/documentation/workshops/development_plan">Development Plan</a> - Future roadmap</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div id="usage" class="section">
        <h2>Current Functionality</h2>
        <p>The current version of the Workshop System provides the following features:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Workshop listing and details</li>
            <li>Administrative tools for creating and managing workshops</li>
            <li>Support for downloadable presentation materials</li>
            <li>Basic presentation viewer</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For detailed instructions on using these features, see the <a href="/documentation/workshops/user_guide">User Guide</a>.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div id="future" class="section">
        <h2>Future Development</h2>
        <p>Development of the Workshop System will follow the roadmap outlined in the <a href="/documentation/workshops/development_plan">Development Plan</a>. Key priorities include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>User-created workshops</li>
            <li>Workshop registration and attendance tracking</li>
            <li>Enhanced presentation management</li>
            <li>Interactive workshop capabilities</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

